works.description: Sotheby’s sale of Magnificent Jewels and Nobel Jewels on May 17 in Geneva was headed by a 10.99 carat fancy intense pink diamond and the most important emerald and diamond tiara to have appeared at auction in over 30 years. The results are out now. The royal tiara, which was formerly in the collection of Princess Katharina Henckel von Donnersmarck circa 1900, went for a record 11.28 million Swiss francs ($12.76 million) to an anonymous buyer.
